      },
      "note" : [ {
        "text" : "Don't change your accent, but do use standard English. Avoid slang, jargon, and local or casual ways of speaking. Even very fluent speakers find these difficult to translate. Don't assume that other people will understand either the sayings you've grown up with or your specialized professional language. If you must use acronyms, take time to explain them.",
